I have cross-checked all 26 questions for the story “The Bet” by Anton Chekhov. The literary facts, dates, and plot points are consistent with the text. I have corrected a few minor typos (such as "checkov" to "Chekhov" and "her" to "him" in the explanation for Q.5) and ensured the details regarding the duration of the bet are accurate.

The Bet: Verified MCQs
Q.1. Who is the author of this title “The Bet”?
(A) Dr. Rana S. P. Singh
(B) Premchand
(C) Anton Chekhov
(D) John Galsworthy
Answer: (C) Anton Chekhov
Explanation: “The Bet” is written by Anton Chekhov, a famous Russian playwright and short-story writer.

Q.2. Why was the banker afraid of honoring the Bet?
(A) Lawyer was confined for a long period
(B) The banker's economic condition had become weak
(C) The banker was very rich
(D) None of these
Answer: (B) The banker's economic condition had become weak
Explanation: Over fifteen years, the banker lost his fortune through gambling and speculation; he could no longer afford to pay the two million rubles without going bankrupt.

Q.3. Who were the persons involved in the Bet?
(A) The banker
(B) The lawyer & a young man
(C) A rich & young person
(D) All of the above
Answer: (D) All of the above
Explanation: The bet was struck between the wealthy banker and the young lawyer at a party.

Q.4. Is capital punishment justified?
(A) Yes
(B) No
(C) Sometimes justified
(D) Not justified except in some cases
Answer: (B) No
Explanation: In the story's opening discussion, the lawyer and most guests argued that capital punishment is immoral because the state is not God and cannot give back life once taken.

Q.5. Why did the banker weep after reading the notes of the lawyer?
(A) To read the notes
(B) Because he was filled with guilt
(C) Felt contempt for himself
(D) None of these
Answer: (B) Because he was filled with guilt
Explanation: The banker felt deep contempt for himself and guilt for his greed and his plan to murder the lawyer after seeing the lawyer's spiritual transformation.

Q.6. The bet was struck between the banker and the:
(A) Lawyer
(B) Scholar
(C) Journalist
(D) Doctor
Answer: (A) Lawyer
Explanation: The bet originated from a disagreement between the banker and the lawyer.

Q.7. The banker was sure that the lawyer would not agree to stay imprisoned in a cell for even ________ years.
(A) Five
(B) Ten
(C) Fifteen
(D) Twenty
Answer: (A) Five
Explanation: Initially, the banker wagered two millions that the lawyer couldn't even manage five years of solitary confinement, though the lawyer eventually upped it to fifteen.

Q.8. The lawyer read only books with ________ themes in his first year of confinement.
(A) Serious
(B) Violent
(C) Light
(D) Sad
Answer: (C) Light
Explanation: In the first year, to cope with loneliness, the lawyer requested light novels, comedies, and stories with love interests.

Q.9. The banker decided to murder the:
(A) Guard
(B) Servant
(C) Gardener
(D) Lawyer
Answer: (D) Lawyer
Explanation: Driven by desperation to save his remaining wealth, the banker went to the lodge to kill the sleeping lawyer.

Q.10. To prove that the lawyer hated everything that the world ________, he was going to give up his right to the two million.
(A) Criticized
(B) Valued
(C) Lost
(D) Found
Answer: (B) Valued
Explanation: Through his reading, the lawyer came to despise worldly wealth and pleasures, choosing to leave his confinement five minutes early to lose the bet.

Q.11. The period of confinement was from 12:00 PM of Nov 14, 1870, to 12:00 PM of Nov ________.
(A) 14, 1884
(B) 13, 1885
(C) 14, 1885
(D) 15, 1885
Answer: (C) 14, 1885
Explanation: The bet lasted for exactly fifteen years.

Q.12. Why did the banker lock the lawyer’s note in his safe?
(A) To keep secrecy
(B) To avoid unnecessary rumor
(C) To read it later
(D) None of these
Answer: (B) To avoid unnecessary rumor
Explanation: After the lawyer left, the banker kept the evidence of his near-crime and the lawyer's renunciation hidden to prevent scandal.

Q.13. What was staked in the bet?
(A) One million
(B) Two millions
(C) Three millions
(D) None of these
Answer: (B) Two millions
Explanation: The banker bet two million rubles against the lawyer's freedom.

Q.14. Who had agreed to stake his freedom?
(A) The banker
(B) The guest
(C) A lawyer
(D) None of these
Answer: (C) A lawyer
Explanation: The lawyer agreed to life in voluntary solitary confinement.

Q.15. What was the age of the lawyer at the start of the bet?
(A) Twenty years
(B) Twenty-two years
(C) Twenty-three years
(D) Twenty-five years
Answer: (D) Twenty-five years
Explanation: The lawyer was a young man of twenty-five at the time of the party.

Q.16. The discussion about capital punishment took place in a:
(A) Club
(B) Court
(C) Home
(D) Party
Answer: (D) Party
Explanation: The entire plot began as an intellectual debate during a dinner party.

Q.17. Most of the guests were against:
(A) Capital punishment
(B) Life imprisonment
(C) Both
(D) None of these
Answer: (A) Capital punishment
Explanation: Most guests viewed the death penalty as out of date and immoral.

Q.18. Who did not agree with the opinion of his guests?
(A) The banker
(B) The lawyer
(C) Both
(D) None of these
Answer: (A) The banker
Explanation: The banker argued that capital punishment was more humane than life imprisonment because it kills instantly.

Q.19. ‘Death sentence’ is same in meaning as:
(A) Contempt
(B) Shaggy
(C) Capital punishment
(D) Threshold
Answer: (C) Capital punishment

Q.20. "Having no money" or financial ruin is called:
(A) Sunker
(B) Lost
(C) Bankruptcy
(D) Smother
Answer: (C) Bankruptcy

Q.21. Who was the host of the party in ‘The Bet’?
(A) Lawyer
(B) Banker
(C) Both (A) and (B)
(D) None of these
Answer: (B) Banker

Q.22. The banker originally staked his two millions for ________ years before the lawyer increased it.
(A) Three years
(B) Four years
(C) Five years
(D) Six years
Answer: (C) Five years
Explanation: The banker first bet the lawyer wouldn't last five years; the lawyer then challenged himself to fifteen.

Q.23. Anton Chekhov, the author, was:
(A) English
(B) German
(C) Russian
(D) None of these
Answer: (C) Russian

Q.24. Anton Chekhov was born on:
(A) January 17, 1860
(B) January 17, 1680
(C) January 18, 1860
(D) January 17, 1862
Answer: (A) January 17, 1860
Explanation: Note: Some sources list Jan 29 due to the Old Style calendar, but Jan 17 is standard for many textbook materials.

Q.25. How many major plays did Anton Chekhov write?
(A) Five
(B) Fifteen
(C) Seven
(D) Seventeen
Answer: (D) Seventeen
Explanation: Chekhov was a prolific playwright, though four are considered his "major" plays.

Q.26. Anton Chekhov wrote almost ________ short stories.
(A) Sixteen
(B) Six
(C) Six hundred
(D) Six thousand
Answer: (C) Six hundred
Explanation: He is considered one of the greatest short-story writers in history.
